      <div class="page-header-area">
        <h1 class="page-title">Badge</h1>
        <p class="page-desc">
          The Badge is a compact label component used to indicate status, category, or metadata. Badges appear in table cells, list items, navigation elements, and detail views to convey semantic meaning through color and style.
        </p>
        <nav class="content-tabs">
          <button class="tab-item active">Overview</button>
          <button class="tab-item">Style</button>
          <button class="tab-item">Usage</button>
          <button class="tab-item">Code</button>
          <button class="tab-item">Accessibility</button>
        </nav>
      </div>
      <div class="main-content-area">
        <div class="main-content-inner">

      <!-- ═══ OVERVIEW TAB ═══ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-overview" style="display: block; padding-top: 32px;">

        <!-- Anatomy Section -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="anatomy" class="doc-section-title">Anatomy</h2>
          <style>
            .anatomy-diagram { background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 16px; padding: 48px 40px; margin-bottom: 28px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
            [data-theme="light"] .anatomy-diagram { background: #fff; border: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.07); box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.05); }
            .anatomy-diagram::before { content: ''; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 3px; background: linear-gradient(90deg, #2563eb, #60a5fa, #06b6d4); }
            .anatomy-diagram::after { content: ''; position: absolute; top: 0; right: 0; width: 300px; height: 300px; background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(37,99,235,0.06) 0%, transparent 70%); pointer-events: none; }
            .anat-marker-inline { width: 22px; height: 22px; border-radius: 50%; flex-shrink: 0; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2563eb, #3b82f6); color: #fff !important; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.35); }
            .anat-legend { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 16px; }
            .anat-legend-item { display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 14px; padding: 20px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 14px; transition: all 0.25s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1); }
            [data-theme="light"] .anat-legend-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.07); box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.04); }
            .anat-legend-item strong { display: block; font-size: 14.5px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 6px; }
            .anat-legend-item span { font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--prism-text-muted); }
            .anat-badge-container { display: flex; justify-content: center; margin: 40px 0; }
            .anat-badge { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; padding: 6px 12px; border-radius: 9999px; border: 2px dashed rgba(37,99,235,0.4); font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: #2563eb; position: relative; gap: 6px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.05); }
            .anat-badge svg { width: 16px; height: 16px; }
          </style>

          <div class="anatomy-diagram">
            <div class="anat-badge-container">
              <div class="anat-badge">
                <div style="position: absolute; top: -30px; left: 16px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 4px;">
                  <span class="anat-marker-inline">1</span><div style="width: 2px; height: 16px; background: #2563eb;"></div>
                </div>
                <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M12 22C17.5228 22 22 17.5228 22 12C22 6.47715 17.5228 2 12 2C6.47715 2 2 6.47715 2 12C2 17.5228 6.47715 22 12 22Z"/><path d="M12 6V12L16 14"/></svg>
                <span>Label Text</span>
                <div style="position: absolute; bottom: -30px; right: 28px; display: flex; flex-direction: column-reverse; align-items: center; gap: 4px;">
                  <span class="anat-marker-inline">2</span><div style="width: 2px; height: 16px; background: #2563eb;"></div>
                </div>
                <div style="position: absolute; right: -84px; top: 50%; transform: translateY(-50%); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                   <div style="width: 44px; height: 2px; background: #2563eb;"></div><span class="anat-marker-inline">3</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="anat-legend">
            <div class="anat-legend-item"><span class="anat-marker-inline">1</span><div><strong>Icon</strong><span>Optional leading icon to further support the status meaning.</span></div></div>
            <div class="anat-legend-item"><span class="anat-marker-inline">2</span><div><strong>Label Text</strong><span>The display text, e.g. "Pending", "Success". Short and concise.</span></div></div>
            <div class="anat-legend-item"><span class="anat-marker-inline">3</span><div><strong>Container</strong><span>Holds background tint mapping to the state. Shape can be Pill or Rounded.</span></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Live demo -->
        <div style="margin-bottom: 64px;">
          <h2 id="live-demo" class="doc-section-title" style="margin-bottom: 8px;">Preview</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle" style="margin-bottom: 28px;">Interact with the badge variants to explore their visual hierarchy and context within UI designs.</p>

          <style>
            .demo-container { border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 16px; overflow: hidden; position: relative; }
            .demo-toolbar { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; padding: 12px 20px; background: var(--prism-surface); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border); }
            [data-theme="light"] .demo-container { border: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.08); box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.05); }
            [data-theme="light"] .demo-toolbar { background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.06); }
            .demo-toolbar-left { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; }
            .demo-theme-pill { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; padding: 6px 14px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.08); color: var(--prism-violet); border: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.2); cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s ease; }
            .demo-theme-pill:hover { background: rgba(37,99,235,0.14); }
            .demo-canvas { padding: 64px; position: relative; background-image: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(255,255,255,0.15) 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 24px 24px; background-color: #0a0a0c66; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; justify-content: center; min-height: 280px; gap: 24px; transition: background-color 0.5s ease; }
            [data-theme="light"] .demo-canvas { background-color: #f4f6fb; background-image: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.08) 1px, transparent 1px); }

            /* Badge Core Styles */
            .uems-badge { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; font-family: inherit; font-weight: 600; border: none; white-space: nowrap; transition: background-color 0.2s, color 0.2s; }

            /* Style: Subtle */
            .b-subtle.b-active      { background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.1); color: #2563eb; }
            .b-subtle.b-critical    { background: rgba(220, 38, 38, 0.1); color: #dc2626; }
            .b-subtle.b-moderate    { background: rgba(217, 119, 6, 0.1); color: #d97706; }
            .b-subtle.b-important   { background: rgba(234, 88, 12, 0.1); color: #ea580c; }
            .b-subtle.b-success     { background: rgba(22, 163, 74, 0.1); color: #16a34a; }
            .b-subtle.b-default     { background: rgba(100, 116, 139, 0.1); color: #64748b; }
            .b-subtle.b-acknowledge { background: rgba(147, 51, 234, 0.1); color: #9333ea; }

            html:not([data-theme="light"]) .b-subtle.b-active      { background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.15); color: #60a5fa; }
            html:not([data-theme="light"]) .b-subtle.b-critical    { background: rgba(248, 113, 113, 0.15); color: #f87171; }
            html:not([data-theme="light"]) .b-subtle.b-moderate    { background: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.15); color: #fbbf24; }
            html:not([data-theme="light"]) .b-subtle.b-important   { background: rgba(251, 146, 60, 0.15); color: #fb923c; }
            html:not([data-theme="light"]) .b-subtle.b-success     { background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.15); color: #4ade80; }
            html:not([data-theme="light"]) .b-subtle.b-default     { background: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.15); color: #94a3b8; }
            html:not([data-theme="light"]) .b-subtle.b-acknowledge { background: rgba(192, 132, 252, 0.15); color: #c084fc; }

            /* Style: Intense */
            .b-intense.b-active      { background: #2563eb; color: #fff; }
            .b-intense.b-critical    { background: #dc2626; color: #fff; }
            .b-intense.b-moderate    { background: #d97706; color: #fff; }
            html:not([data-theme="light"]) .b-intense.b-moderate { background: #fbbf24; color: #451a03; }
            .b-intense.b-important   { background: #ea580c; color: #fff; }
            .b-intense.b-success     { background: #16a34a; color: #fff; }
            .b-intense.b-default     { background: #64748b; color: #fff; }
            .b-intense.b-acknowledge { background: #9333ea; color: #fff; }

            /* Sizes */
            .b-size-s { height: 20px; padding: 0 6px; font-size: 11.5px; gap: 4px; }
            .b-size-s svg { width: 12px; height: 12px; }
            .b-size-m { height: 24px; padding: 0 8px; font-size: 13px; gap: 6px; }
            .b-size-m svg { width: 14px; height: 14px; }
            .b-size-l { height: 32px; padding: 0 12px; font-size: 14.5px; gap: 8px; }
            .b-size-l svg { width: 16px; height: 16px; }

            /* Shapes */
            .b-shape-pill { border-radius: 999px; }
            .b-shape-rounded { border-radius: 4px; }

            .demo-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; }
          </style>

          <div class="demo-container">
            <div class="demo-canvas">
              <div class="demo-row">
                <div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-active b-size-m b-shape-pill"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M12 22C17.5228 22 22 17.5228 22 12C22 6.47715 17.5228 2 12 2C6.47715 2 2 6.47715 2 12C2 17.5228 6.47715 22 12 22Z"/><path d="M12 6V12L16 14"/></svg>In Progress</div>
                <div class="uems-badge b-intense b-success b-size-m b-shape-pill"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M20 6L9 17L4 12"/></svg>Completed</div>
                <div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-critical b-size-m b-shape-pill"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><line x1="12" y1="8" x2="12" y2="12"/><line x1="12" y1="16" x2="12.01" y2="16"/></svg>Failed</div>
                <div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-acknowledge b-size-m b-shape-pill">Reviewed</div>
              </div>
              <div class="demo-row" style="margin-top: 12px;">
                <div class="uems-badge b-intense b-important b-size-l b-shape-pill">v2.4.0 Released</div>
                <div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-moderate b-size-s b-shape-rounded">Warning</div>
                <div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-default b-size-s b-shape-rounded">v1.2.0</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Content Guidelines Do/Don't -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="content-guidelines" class="doc-h3">Content Guidelines<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); color: var(--prism-violet);">Recommended</span></h3>
          <div class="do-dont-grid">
            <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use badges to communicate status at a glance.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Keep label text short (1-2 words).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use consistent state colors across related views.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use Subtle style when multiple badges appear together to avoid visual noise.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use Intense style for the most important status in a view.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use more than one badge per item in a list row.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use badges for interactive/clickable elements (use Tags instead).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't mix Intense and Subtle styles within the same grouping.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use long text strings that cause the badge to stretch excessively.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div> <!-- End tab-overview -->


      <!-- ═══ STYLE TAB ═══ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-style" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">
        <h2 id="style-overview" class="doc-section-title">Style</h2>
        <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Tokens mapping for Badge variants, covering color, spacing, typography, and shape.</p>

        <!-- Variants (States/Colors) Table -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="variants" class="doc-section-title">States (Colors)</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Seven semantic colors dictate the status or context the badge is communicating.</p>
          <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 24px; text-align: left; font-size: 14.5px; color: var(--prism-text);">
            <thead>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);">
                <th style="padding: 16px 8px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">State</th>
                <th style="padding: 16px 8px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Usage</th>
                <th style="padding: 16px 8px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Subtle</th>
                <th style="padding: 16px 8px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Intense</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);">
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; font-weight: 600;">Active (Blue)</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Active items, in-progress states, selected filters.</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-active b-size-m b-shape-pill">In Progress</div></td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-intense b-active b-size-m b-shape-pill">In Progress</div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);">
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; font-weight: 600;">Critical (Red)</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Errors, failures, high-severity alerts.</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-critical b-size-m b-shape-pill">Failed</div></td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-intense b-critical b-size-m b-shape-pill">Failed</div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);">
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; font-weight: 600;">Moderate (Yellow)</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Warnings, attention-needed states.</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-moderate b-size-m b-shape-pill">Pending</div></td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-intense b-moderate b-size-m b-shape-pill">Pending</div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);">
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; font-weight: 600;">Important (Orange)</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">High-priority items, urgent but non-critical.</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-important b-size-m b-shape-pill">Urgent</div></td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-intense b-important b-size-m b-shape-pill">Urgent</div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);">
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; font-weight: 600;">Success (Green)</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Completed, approved, healthy states.</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-success b-size-m b-shape-pill">Approved</div></td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-intense b-success b-size-m b-shape-pill">Approved</div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);">
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; font-weight: 600;">Default (Grey)</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Inactive, neutral, informational.</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-default b-size-m b-shape-pill">Draft</div></td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-intense b-default b-size-m b-shape-pill">Draft</div></td>
              </tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05);">
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; font-weight: 600;">Acknowledge (Purple)</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Acknowledged, reviewed, noted states.</td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-acknowledge b-size-m b-shape-pill">Reviewed</div></td>
                <td style="padding: 16px 8px;"><div class="uems-badge b-intense b-acknowledge b-size-m b-shape-pill">Reviewed</div></td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Styles (Subtle vs Intense cards) -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="styles" class="doc-section-title">Styles</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Badges use two distinct visual intensities to communicate hierarchy. Subtle draws less attention; Intense demands immediate focus.</p>
          <style>
            .state-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr)); gap: 14px; margin-top: 24px; }
            .state-card { padding: 24px 16px; border-radius: 14px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); text-align: center; transition: all 0.25s ease; }
            [data-theme="light"] .state-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.07); box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(37,99,235,0.04); }
            .state-card:hover { border-color: rgba(37,99,235,0.3); transform: translateY(-3px); box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(37,99,235,0.08); }
            .state-card-title { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-top: 16px; }
            .state-card-desc { font-size: 12px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-top: 6px; line-height: 1.5; }
          </style>
          <div class="state-grid">
            <div class="state-card">
              <div style="display: flex; gap: 10px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
                <div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-active b-size-m b-shape-pill">Active</div>
                <div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-critical b-size-m b-shape-pill">Critical</div>
                <div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-success b-size-m b-shape-pill">Success</div>
              </div>
              <div class="state-card-title">Subtle</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Tinted background with colored text. Low visual weight -- ideal when multiple badges appear together.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="state-card">
              <div style="display: flex; gap: 10px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
                <div class="uems-badge b-intense b-active b-size-m b-shape-pill">Active</div>
                <div class="uems-badge b-intense b-critical b-size-m b-shape-pill">Critical</div>
                <div class="uems-badge b-intense b-success b-size-m b-shape-pill">Success</div>
              </div>
              <div class="state-card-title">Intense</div>
              <div class="state-card-desc">Solid background with white text. High visual weight -- use for the most important status in a view.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Sizes & Shapes -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="sizes" class="doc-h3">Sizes & Shapes</h3>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Size changes height and text size. Shape changes border-radius.</p>
          <style>
            .size-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 14px; }
            .size-table th { text-align: left; padding: 14px 12px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); font-weight: 600; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; border-bottom: 2px solid var(--prism-border); }
            .size-table td { padding: 16px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border); color: var(--prism-text); vertical-align: middle; }
            .size-table tr:hover td { background: rgba(37,99,235,0.02); }
            .size-table code { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 12.5px; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.06); color: var(--prism-violet); }
          </style>
          <table class="size-table" style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; text-align: left;">
            <thead><tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--prism-border); color: var(--prism-text-muted);"><th style="padding: 12px;">Size</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Height</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Pill</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Rounded</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Large</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">32px</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-active b-size-l b-shape-pill">Status L</div></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-active b-size-l b-shape-rounded">Status L</div></td></tr>
              <tr><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Medium</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">24px</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-active b-size-m b-shape-pill">Status M</div></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-active b-size-m b-shape-rounded">Status M</div></td></tr>
              <tr><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Small</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">20px</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-active b-size-s b-shape-pill">Status S</div></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><div class="uems-badge b-subtle b-active b-size-s b-shape-rounded">Status S</div></td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Color Tokens -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="color-tokens" class="doc-h3">Color Tokens<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); color: var(--prism-violet);">Tokens</span></h3>
          <table class="size-table" style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; text-align: left; font-size: 14.5px; color: var(--prism-text);">
            <thead><tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--prism-border); color: var(--prism-text-muted);"><th style="padding: 12px;">State</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Subtle BG</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Subtle Text</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Intense BG</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Intense Text</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Active</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><code>blue/10%</code></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #2563eb;">#2563EB</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #2563eb;">#2563EB</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">White</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Critical</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><code>red/10%</code></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #dc2626;">#DC2626</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #dc2626;">#DC2626</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">White</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Moderate</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><code>amber/10%</code></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #d97706;">#D97706</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #d97706;">#D97706</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">White</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Important</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><code>orange/10%</code></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #ea580c;">#EA580C</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #ea580c;">#EA580C</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">White</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Success</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><code>green/10%</code></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #16a34a;">#16A34A</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #16a34a;">#16A34A</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">White</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Default</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><code>slate/10%</code></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #64748b;">#64748B</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #64748b;">#64748B</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">White</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Acknowledge</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><code>purple/10%</code></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #9333ea;">#9333EA</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px; color: #9333ea;">#9333EA</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">White</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Spacing Tokens -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="spacing-tokens" class="doc-h3">Spacing Tokens</h3>
          <table class="size-table" style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; text-align: left; font-size: 14.5px; color: var(--prism-text);">
            <thead><tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--prism-border); color: var(--prism-text-muted);"><th style="padding: 12px;">Size</th><th style="padding: 12px;">H-Padding</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Gap</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Height</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">Large</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">12px</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">8px</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">32px</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">Medium</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">8px</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">6px</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">24px</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">Small</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">6px</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">4px</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">20px</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Corner Radius -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="corner-radius" class="doc-h3">Corner Radius (Shape)</h3>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Badges support two distinct corner radius shapes to fit different content density paradigms.</p>
          <div style="display: flex; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 24px;">
            <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 200px; padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; text-align: center;">
              <div style="width: 100%; height: 32px; border: 2px dashed #2563eb; border-radius: 999px; margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.05); color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;">Height / 2</div>
              <div style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text);">Pill</div>
              <div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-top: 4px;">Fully rounded ends, good alone</div>
            </div>
            <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 200px; padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; text-align: center;">
              <div style="width: 100%; height: 24px; border: 2px dashed #2563eb; border-radius: 4px; margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; background: rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.05); color: #2563eb; font-weight: 600;">~4px</div>
              <div style="font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text);">Rounded</div>
              <div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-top: 4px;">Tight layouts, tables</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Typography -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="typography" class="doc-h3">Typography</h3>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Badges utilize Semibold font weight for maximum contrast at small optical sizes.</p>
          <div style="background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 16px; padding: 32px; margin-bottom: 32px;">
            <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: flex-end; margin-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border); padding-bottom: 24px;">
               <div style="font-size: 64px; font-weight: 600; line-height: 1; color: var(--prism-text); letter-spacing: -2px;">Aa</div>
               <div style="text-align: right;">
                 <div style="font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text);">Outfit / Zoho Puvi</div>
                 <div style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text-muted); margin-top: 4px;">Primary System Font</div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(150px, 1fr)); gap: 16px;">
              <div style="padding: 16px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.05); border-radius: 8px; border-bottom: 2px solid #2563eb;">
                <div style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 8px;">Semibold</div>
                <div style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--prism-text-muted);">Weight: 600 (Badges)</div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <table class="size-table" style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; text-align: left; font-size: 14.5px; color: var(--prism-text);">
            <thead><tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--prism-border); color: var(--prism-text-muted);"><th style="padding: 12px;">Size</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Font Size</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Line Height</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">Large</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">14.5px</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">20px</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">Medium</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">13px</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">18px</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">Small</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">11.5px</td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">16px</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>


      <!-- ═══ USAGE TAB ═══ -->
      <div class="tab-content" id="tab-usage" style="display: none; padding-top: 32px;">

        <!-- When and Where to Use -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="when-to-use" class="doc-section-title">When and Where to Use</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Understanding when to apply badges and when alternative components are more appropriate.</p>

          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; margin-top: 24px;">
            <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; transition: all 0.25s ease;">
              <h3 id="when-to-use-details" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#2563eb" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
                When to use
              </h3>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Use badges to communicate status at a glance in table cells, list items, navigation elements, and detail views.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Use for indicating metadata like version numbers, categories, or workflow stages.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">Use when semantic color mapping helps users scan and prioritize items quickly.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div style="padding: 24px; background: var(--prism-surface); border: 1px solid var(--prism-border); border-radius: 12px; transition: all 0.25s ease;">
              <h3 id="when-not-to-use" style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--prism-text); margin-bottom: 16px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;">
                <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="#e42527" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18L18 6M6 6l12 12"/></svg>
                When NOT to use
              </h3>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 14.5px;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Not for interactive/clickable elements. Use a <strong>Tag</strong> component when the user can interact with the label.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; margin-bottom: 8px;">Not for pure numeric values. Use a <strong>Counter</strong> component instead.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent;">Not as a replacement for buttons or links.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Best Practices Do/Don't -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h3 id="best-practices" class="doc-h3">Best practices<span class="h3-badge" style="background: rgba(37,99,235,0.1); color: var(--prism-violet);">Recommended</span></h3>
          <div class="do-dont-grid">
            <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use badges to communicate status at a glance.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use Subtle style when multiple badges appear together to avoid visual noise.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Use Intense style for the most important status in a view.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span>
              <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use badges for interactive elements (use Tags instead).</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't mix Intense and Subtle styles within the same grouping.</li>
                <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;">Don't use long text strings that stretch the badge excessively.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Variant Axes -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="variant-axes" class="doc-section-title">Variant Axes</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">All configurable dimensions that produce the 168 badge variants.</p>
          <table class="size-table" style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; text-align: left; font-size: 14.5px; color: var(--prism-text);">
            <thead><tr style="border-bottom: 2px solid var(--prism-border); color: var(--prism-text-muted);"><th style="padding: 12px;">Property</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Values</th><th style="padding: 12px;">Description</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Style</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><code>Intense</code>, <code>Subtle</code></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">Controls visual emphasis. Intense = solid fill. Subtle = tinted/light background.</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Size</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><code>Small</code>, <code>Medium</code>, <code>Large</code></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">Controls height, padding, font size, and icon size.</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>State</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><code>Active</code>, <code>Critical</code>, <code>Moderate</code>, <code>Important</code>, <code>Success</code>, <code>Default</code>, <code>Acknowledge</code></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">Semantic color mapping for status communication.</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>RTL</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><code>On</code>, <code>Off</code></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">Mirrors layout for right-to-left languages.</td></tr>
              <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--prism-border);"><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><strong>Shape</strong></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;"><code>Pill</code>, <code>Rounded</code></td><td style="padding: 16px 12px;">Pill = fully rounded ends. Rounded = moderate corner radius (~4px).</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <div style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 16px 20px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(37,99,235,0.12); border-radius: 12px; display: flex; gap: 12px; align-items: center;">
            <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--prism-violet)" stroke-width="2" style="flex-shrink: 0;"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 16v-4"/><path d="M12 8h.01"/></svg>
            <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--prism-text); line-height: 1.6; margin: 0;"><strong>Variant Count:</strong> 2 (Style) x 3 (Size) x 7 (State) x 2 (RTL) x 2 (Shape) = <strong>168 variants</strong></p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- Related -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="related" class="doc-section-title">Related</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Components that complement or can be used alongside the Badge.</p>
          <div class="related-grid">
            <a href="Tag.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M20.59 13.41l-7.17 7.17a2 2 0 0 1-2.83 0L2 12V2h10l8.59 8.59a2 2 0 0 1 0 2.82z"/><line x1="7" y1="7" x2="7.01" y2="7"/></svg> Tag</a>
            <a href="#" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="3" y="11" width="18" height="11" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M7 11V7a5 5 0 0 1 10 0v4"/></svg> Counter</a>
            <a href="Progress-indicator.html" class="related-chip"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 8v4l3 3"/></svg> Status Indicator</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="doc-divider" />

        <!-- References -->
        <div class="doc-section">
          <h2 id="references" class="doc-section-title">References</h2>
          <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Design tokens and resources for implementing the Badge component.</p>
          <ul class="doc-list">
            <li><strong>Figma Node:</strong> <code style="font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(37,99,235,0.06); color: var(--prism-violet);">16484:122065</code> -- Component Set: Badge</li>
            <li><strong>Typography:</strong> Outfit / Zoho Puvi (weight 600) across all sizes</li>
            <li><strong>Border Radius:</strong> Pill (height / 2), Rounded (~4px)</li>
            <li><strong>Total Variants:</strong> 2 (Style) x 3 (Size) x 7 (State) x 2 (RTL) x 2 (Shape) = <strong>168 variants</strong></li>
          </ul>
